      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "7IabMh4TsMG9",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "7IabMh4TsMG9"
      },
      "source": [
        "# Zero-Shot Chess Opening Move Prediction with Meta-Learning\n",
        "\n",
        "This notebook trains two models for next-move prediction in chess openings:\n",
        "\n",
        "- a supervised baseline trained on all non-held-out openings\n",
        "- a first-order MAML model trained episodically to adapt to a new opening from a few support examples\n",
        "\n",
        "The default data source is the public Hugging Face dataset [`Lichess/chess-openings`](https://huggingface.co/datasets/Lichess/chess-openings), which currently provides `eco`, `name`, `pgn`, `uci`, and `epd` fields. The notebook also includes optional loaders for a Kaggle CSV export or raw Lichess PGN games.\n",
        "\n",
        "## Colab notes\n",
        "\n",
        "- Runtime: Python 3.11\n",
        "- Recommended: `Runtime -> Change runtime type -> T4 GPU`\n",
        "- If you want to use a raw PGN file, upload it to `/content/` first\n",
        "- The held-out opening is completely excluded from meta-training and baseline training\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 1,
      "id": "6BVm8CmFsMG_",
