      "source": [
        "fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(12, 4))\n",
        "\n",
        "baseline_epochs = [row['epoch'] for row in baseline_history]\n",
        "baseline_losses = [row['train_loss'] for row in baseline_history]\n",
        "baseline_accs = [row['train_acc'] for row in baseline_history]\n",
        "maml_steps = [row['step'] for row in maml_history]\n",
        "maml_losses = [row['meta_loss'] for row in maml_history]\n",
        "maml_accs = [row['meta_acc'] for row in maml_history]\n",
        "\n",
        "axes[0].plot(baseline_epochs, baseline_losses, label='Baseline train loss')\n",
        "axes[0].plot(maml_steps, maml_losses, label='MAML meta loss')\n",
        "axes[0].set_title('Training losses')\n",
        "axes[0].legend()\n",
        "\n",
        "axes[1].plot(baseline_epochs, baseline_accs, label='Baseline train acc')\n",
        "axes[1].plot(maml_steps, maml_accs, label='MAML meta acc')\n",
        "axes[1].set_title('Training accuracies')\n",
        "axes[1].legend()\n",
        "plt.show()\n",
        "\n",
        "results_df.plot(x='stage', y='top1_accuracy', kind='bar', figsize=(8, 4), title='Held-out opening Top-1 accuracy')\n",
        "plt.ylim(0, 1)\n",
        "plt.show()\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "9_8gv14esMHH",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "9_8gv14esMHH"
      },
      "source": [
        "## How to adapt this notebook\n",
        "\n",
        "- To reserve a specific opening for zero-shot testing, set `cfg.holdout_task` to the exact opening name or ECO code.\n",
        "- To group tasks more coarsely, switch `cfg.task_group_field` from `'name'` to `'eco'`.\n",
        "- To use raw Lichess games instead of curated opening lines, upload a `.pgn` file and set `cfg.data_source = 'pgn_file'`.\n",
        "- To train longer, increase `cfg.baseline_epochs` and `cfg.meta_steps`.\n",
        "- To make evaluation more stable, repeat `build_holdout_episode(...)` with different seeds and average the metrics.\n"
      ]
    }
  ],
